<br>
Assigning &gt;&gt;&gt; Randoming in almost all situations. Point system might be the only alternative to assigning that really works fairly. <br>
<br>
Only problem with point system is that you end up with a lot of stuff nobody wants... then again you also end up with super decked out chars that only a point system can achieve (compare AfterLife to Fires of Heaven for instance). <br>
<br>
I think your problem with Finite.. and thus the non-randoming system... was leadership. Good Leadership = Good assignment of loot. If your leadership is biased/bad to begin with then I guess randoming would be a good way to go at it. <br>
<br>
Just think of the best case scenarios of each system:<br>
Assignment = Loot is assigned to best serve the guild as a whole. <br>
Points = Loot is assigned to best represent participation.<br>
Random = Loot is completely randomly assigned. <br>
<br>
Which comes down to:<br>
Assignment = Best for strength of a guild.<br>
Points = Fairest method for the individual.<br>
Random = Everything is left to chance... which can be good or bad. <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uugle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ugle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kindly Poster</span><br>  Posts: 444<br> <font color=#778899>(12/19/01 6:03:47 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://ugleduklin.tripod.com/sitebuildercontent/sitebuilderpictures/dscn0011s.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How do guilds handle loot for people who like to play al</span><hr size=1> Or depending on the Guild..<br>
<br>
Assignment = the GL and her twinks and her RL Friends Twinks get all the loot, even if it's a minor upgrade for them and a big upgrade for others.  I mean, the GL's L35 Warrior twink would make much better use of a SS MQ for a BP as an upgrade to their KD BP then the Guilds 57 Warrior would who's wearing Barbed Ringmail.<br>
<br>
Points = Good for those who have time to participate.  Should a L46 Warrior get the Indico BP for showing up to the most raids over say a 56 Warrior who's the Guild's main tank?  Points are good to encourage participation.  Points are bad for distributing loot or to work on weaknesses.  Points mean that if you have a 10/19 weapon and a 10/18 weapon drops, you get that over someone using a 10/21 weapon.  Fair to the individual, but IMO not to the Guild.<br>
<br>
Random = Same type of thing as above.  Random doesn't take into account who would put the item to the best use, it rewards who rolls the best.  And I know some people who I have seen NOT win a roll maybe 3 times out of 25 or so.  I'm missing something somewhere on how they do that I think.<br>
<br>
In a good Guild with leaders who are really looking out for the Guild overall, I would prefer assignment.  It means sometimes your feelings will get hurt, but if YOU are working towards making the Guild stronger as a whole, then you will understand and accept their judgement.  I kinda like a mixture, where things like BP's or MQ drops are assigned, stuff like Bracers or Gauntlets are randomed, but you need to have people working together.  When some arms dropped in PoG, the Warrior who won them gave me her Cobalt ones.  No discussion, she asked if they were an upgrade to my Indico and gave them to me.  I've passed on the Gauntlets because our DE Warriors could use the +STR on them over me.<br>
<br>
In a pick-up group though, I'm a firm believer in full randoms.  Most camps drop items only specific classes can use, but you need balanced groups to be efficient.  So it might suck when that Cleric wins the Fungi, but then again, you wouldn't have won it in the first place without them... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/urykarderashken.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rykar Derashken</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dubious Poster</span><br>  Posts: 159<br> <font color=#778899>(12/20/01 2:51:45 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://rykar.home.mindspring.com/megaman.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How do guilds handle loot for people who like to play al</span><hr size=1> /beat dead horse<br>
